Why centrifugal force is a "Phantom Force"
===================================
When on a spinning a circle, you are moving tangent to the circle, however, the friction between your butt and the surface acts kind of like a rope keeping you attached to the center. Causing you to move in a curve. When you lose that friction, you still move tangent to the circle (tangent is the line 90 degrees from the radius) which gives the effect of it pushing you away. (We are covering that in my physics class right now).
